\begin_layout Abstract
We classify multi-peak ground-state configurations of the stationary nonlinear Schrödinger equation 
\begin_inset Formula $(-\Delta+V+E)\psi+\sigma|\psi|^{2p}\psi=0$
\end_inset

 in the high-energy regime 
\begin_inset Formula $E\to\infty$
\end_inset

. Using the rescaling and concentration compactness framework of Kirr and Natarajan
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
after ""
key "KirrNatarajan2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, ground states decompose into well-separated profiles whose positions are governed by a finite-dimensional algebraic system balancing the Hessian 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV(x_0)$
\end_inset

 of the potential against nonlinear inter-peak interactions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
We prove that near a non-degenerate local maximum 
\begin_inset Formula $x_0$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

, the admissible multi-peak configurations are: collinear arrangements along a single eigenvector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV$
\end_inset

; isosceles triangles requiring the eigenvalue constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_2=3\lambda_1$
\end_inset

; equilateral triangles requiring 
\begin_inset Formula $|\lambda_2|/|\lambda_1|\geq 3$
\end_inset

; and equilateral triangles with a continuous rotational degree of freedom 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

, admissible for all orientations when 
\begin_inset Formula $\tfrac{1}{3}\leq\mu\leq 3$
\end_inset

 (where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=|\lambda_2|/|\lambda_1|$
\end_inset

) and for restricted angular windows otherwise. To extend these to finite energy, we construct explicit solutions of the perturbation system 
\begin_inset Formula $F_i(\delta y,R)=0$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $R=0$
\end_inset

, identify the four-dimensional kernel of the linearization, and show that gauge-fixing constraints reduce the problem to a system amenable to the implicit function theorem.
\end_layout

