\begin_layout Standard
Projecting onto the translational modes yields the reduced system. We introduce the following quantities:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition

\begin_inset Argument 1
status collapsed


\begin_layout Standard
Interaction functional and coefficients
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "def:interaction"

\end_inset

 The 
\emph on
interaction functional
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula \[
Q_R(z) = -\sigma\,\bigl\langle \partial_{z/|z|} u_R(\cdot - z),\, u_R^{2p+1} \bigr\rangle_{L^2}.
\]
\end_inset

The 
\emph on
minimum inter-peak distance
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula $m_R = \min\{|z_j(R)-z_i(R)| : i\neq j\}$
\end_inset

. The 
\emph on
interaction coefficients
\emph default
 are 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}\label{eq:alpha-def}
\alpha_{ki} = \frac{Q_R(|z_k-z_i|)}{Q_R(m_R)}, \quad\text{satisfying } 0\leq\alpha_{ki}\leq 1,
\end{equation}
\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}=1$
\end_inset

 precisely when 
\begin_inset Formula $|z_k-z_i|=m_R$
\end_inset

 (nearest neighbors). 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset Separator plain

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition

\begin_inset Argument 1
status collapsed


\begin_layout Standard
Overall interaction strength
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "def:chi"

\end_inset

 The 
\emph on
overall interaction strength
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}\label{eq:chi-def}
\chi = \frac{2\,Q_R(m_R)}{\norm{u_R}_{L^2}^2\,R^4\,m_R} > 0.
\end{equation}
\end_inset

This is a single positive scalar that captures the magnitude of the inter-peak interaction relative to the Hessian restoring force. It is 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 equal to any individual 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}$
\end_inset

; rather, the force on peak 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 from peak 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 has magnitude 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}\chi$
\end_inset

. 
\end_layout

