\begin_inset Formula $y_i^U\in U$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_i^S\in U^\perp$
\end_inset

. Applying the projection 
\begin_inset Formula $P_S$
\end_inset

 onto the stable subspace (
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda>0$
\end_inset

) to
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:algebraic"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV P_S y_i = \chi\sum_{k\in N_i}\alpha_{ki}P_S(y_k-y_i)$
\end_inset

. Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV|_{U^\perp}$
\end_inset

 has all positive eigenvalues and 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi>0$
\end_inset

