\end_inset

Set 
\begin_inset Formula $2a=1$
\end_inset

, giving 
\begin_inset Formula $a=1/2$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $h=1/\sqrt{3}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $|y_k-y_i|=1$
\end_inset

 for all pairs. All three pairs are nearest neighbors. From 
\begin_inset Formula $y_1$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{12}=\alpha_{13}=-\lambda_2/3$
\end_inset

 as before. From 
\begin_inset Formula $y_2$
\end_inset

 (with both 
\begin_inset Formula $y_1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_3$
\end_inset

